scopecontent.p:
This is a collection of materials related to personnel of the University.
                    Included in the collection are: class roll and record books of Rev. Edward F.
                    Jenkins, O.S.A., 1942-1976; student grade book of Rev. T.F. Hartley, 1892-1893;
                    memoirs and histories by George F. Riley, including Riley Remembers (1935-2000);
                    disbound scrapbooks kept by Edwin T. Grimes (1880-1953); obituaries and programs
                    from funeral masses; news clippings about faculty and administration personnel;
                    programs; and publications by University faculty/personnel. Additionally the
                    collection contains research by Francis E. Tourscher on work of religious
                    sisters during the flu epidemic of 1918.
